== Cilantro-Lime Forbidden Rice ==

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Halve, peel, and finely chop the @red onion{1}.

Start the cilantro-lime forbidden rice: heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a #medium pot{} over medium heat. Add the red onion and cook, tossing, ~{4-5%minutes}, until softened. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the @black Thai rice{3%cups} and toss to coat. Add @water{1 1/2%cups} and a large pinch of salt to the #pot, bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a simmer for ~{30-35%minutes}, until tender.

== Spicy Plum Relish ==

Meanwhile, prep ingredients: halve, pit, and finely dice the @plum{1}. Halve the @lime{1}. Chop the @cilantro{1%bunch}. Mince the @jalapeño{1}, removing the seeds if you prefer less heat. Thinly slice the @Swiss chard{1%bunch}, including the stems, into ribbons.

Make the plum salsa: in a #small bowl{}, combine the diced plum, the juice of half the lime, a pinch of cilantro, and as much jalapeño as you dare. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Pork Chops ==

Cook the pork: heat @oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large oven-proof pan{} over medium-high heat. Season the @pork chops{2} on all sides with the @BBQ spice rub{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Add pork chops to the pan and cook ~{2-3%minutes} per side, until golden brown but not yet cooked through.

Brush or spoon the @hoisin sauce{1%tablespoon} on top of the pork chops. Transfer the pan to the oven to finish cooking for ~{5-6%minutes}, until just barely pink in the center. Alternately, if you don't have an oven-proof pan, transfer the pork to a #baking sheet{} and cook as directed. Set pork aside to rest for ~{5%minutes}.

== Finish ==

Once the rice is cooked, stir the Swiss chard. Cover, and steam for ~{5%minutes}, then stir in the remaining cilantro and a squeeze of lime. Season with salt and pepper.

> Our smoky BBQ spice rub pairs unexpectedly well with sweet hoisin sauce for a sweet-and-spicy pork chop glaze. Tangy, juicy plum and jalapeño mirror that same flavor combo in a vibrant, sweet relish on top. Tender Swiss chard is folded into hearty forbidden rice for a colorful and tasty side.